properties.Title: Heat Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Humidex values reaching 33 are expected for the next 3 days. Heat event begins today. Temperatures are expected to reach near 30 degrees today until Saturday. Humidex values will likely reach the mid to upper thirties on Friday and Saturday. Temperatures overnight will remain near twenty, providing little relief from the heat. Hot and humid air can also bring deteriorating air quality and can result in the Air Quality Health Index to approach the high risk category. Somewhat cooler and less humid air will arrive on Sunday. ### The risks are greater for young children, pregnant women, older adults, people with chronic illnesses and people working or exercising outdoors. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ONStorm.
